As high-summer approaches, the crepe myrtle in Nantong City of east China's Jiangsu Province welcomes its peak blooming period. Streets, river banks and parks are all adorned by the purplish clouds of the common street plant, which is hardy to drought. The flower can be seen from June to September. (All images via CFP.) (If you want to contribute and have specific expertise, please contact us at nature@cgtn.com.)